BEGIN_PGML

>>[@ image( "UBC-SM-18-003.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*<<

A tower is made of three uniform cylindrical segments [`AB`], [`BC`], and [`CD`] of diameter [`d_1`], [`d_2`], and [`d_3`], respectively.  It carries a load of [`M_1=[$m1]`] [`kg`] mass at the top at [`A`], a platform (deck) at [`B`] which is anchored using cables with a net vertical upward force [`P = [$p]g`] [`N`], and another load of mass [`M_2=[$m2]`] [`kg`] at [`C`].
1.	Determine the internal axial force distribution in the three segments of the tower. What is the ground reaction (at [`D`]) on the tower?
2.	If [`d_2=[$d2]`] [`m`], determine [`d_1`] and [`d_3`] such that the average axial normal stress is uniform (i.e., constant) along the tower. 

_Note: Assume the tower segments and the platform to be relatively light_.

[`F_{AB}=`] [____]{"$ab"} [`N`]  
[`F_{BC}=`] [____]{"$bc"} [`N`]  
[`F_{CD}=`] [____]{"$cd"} [`N`]  
[`d_1=`] [____]{"$d1"} [`m`]  
[`d_3=`] [____]{"$d3"} [`m`]  
  
END_PGML


